{"repository": {"pullRequest": {"number": 896, "title": "docs(cli): add missing '-m' flag to 'python birdnet_analyzer.train' invocation", "body": "## Summary\n\n\\`docs/usage/cli.rst\\` step 4 told users to run:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\npython birdnet_analyzer.train <path to training data folder> -o <...>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nBut \\`birdnet_analyzer.train\\` is a module, not a script path \u2014 the invocation needs \\`-m\\`. The working example a few lines below (line 170) already uses \\`python -m birdnet_analyzer.train train_data/ -o ...\\`. Fixed step 4 to match.\n\nCloses #895\n\n## Testing\n\nDocs-only. Added missing \\`-m\\` flag to match the example further down the same file.", "baseRefName": "main", "baseRefOid": "30cc44b8273af0a032401714f79125964711593c", "baseRepository": {"nameWithOwner": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer"}, "url": "https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/pull/896", "createdAt": "2026-04-21T06:12:05Z", "mergedAt": "2026-04-21T16:38:29Z"}}, "base": {"repo": {"full_name": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer"}, "sha": "30cc44b8273af0a032401714f79125964711593c"}, "diff_url": "https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/pull/896.diff", "number": 896, "created_at": "2026-04-21T06:12:05Z", "merged_at": "2026-04-21T16:38:29Z", "resolved_issues": [895]}
